OL,3,CNewcastle man handed suspended
OL,4,Csentence over offensive tweets
OL,6,FHe was handed a 16-month jail term
OL,7,Fsuspended for two years. As a
OL,8,Frequirement of his sentence, the judge
OL,9,Fsaid Thompson's use of the internet
OL,10,Fshould be closely monitored by police
OL,11,For probation officers.
OL,13,FDetective Chief Superintendent James
OL,14,FDunkerley, Head of Counter Terrorism
OL,15,FPolicing North East, said:
OL,17,F"The Counter Terrorism Policing
OL,18,Fnetwork works around the clock to
OL,19,Fidentify harmful content online and
OL,20,Fbring to justice anyone promoting such
OL,21,Fmaterial on social media.
